NEW YORK TRAP ROCK CORPORATION, as Owner of THE Scow EDNA, Libelant-Appellee, v. THE Steam Tug S. L. CROSBY, Cornell Steamboat Company, Claimant-Appellant, and THE Dredge LAKE ELLENDALE, National Dredging Company, Claimant-Appellee. No. 364. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Decided May 2, 1932. Kirlin, Campbell, Hickox, Keating & MeGrann, of New York City (Robert S. Er-skine and Henry P. Elliott, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Frederick W. Park, of New York City, for libelant-appellee. Bigham, Englar, Jones & Houston, of New York City (Charles A. Van Hagen, Jr., of New York City, of counsel), for claimant-appellee.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS' N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
